def file2matrix(filename):
    """
    
    parameters:
        fileName - 
    return:
        featureMat - 
        classLabelVector - (didntLike - 0, smallDoses - 1, largeDoses - 2)
    """
    data = pd.read_table(filename, header=None)    # PandasDataFrame
    data.iloc[:,3]=data.iloc[:,3].map({'didntLike': 0, 'smallDoses': 1, 'largeDoses': 2})
    featureMat = data.iloc[:,:3]
    classLabelVector = data.iloc[:,3]
    # featureMat = featureMat.values.tolist()      # DataFrameMatrix
    # classLabelVector = classLabelVector.values.tolist()  
    
    featureMat = np.array(featureMat)      # DataFrameNdarray(Numpy)
    classLabelVector = np.array(classLabelVector)  

    return featureMat, classLabelVector

def showdatas1(datingDataMat, datingLabels):
    """
    np.argwher()
    parameters:
        datingDataMat - 
        datingLabels - (didntLike - 0, smallDoses - 1, largeDoses - 2)
    """
    didntLike = np.array(datingDataMat)[np.argwhere(np.array(datingLabels) == 0)]
    didntLike.resize(didntLike.shape[0], didntLike.shape[2])
    smallDoses = np.array(datingDataMat)[np.argwhere(np.array(datingLabels) == 1)]
    smallDoses.resize(smallDoses.shape[0], smallDoses.shape[2])
    largeDoses = np.array(datingDataMat)[np.argwhere(np.array(datingLabels) == 2)]
    largeDoses.resize(largeDoses.shape[0], largeDoses.shape[2])
    
    plt.figure(figsize=[18,6])
    plt.scatter(didntLike[:,0],didntLike[:,1],label='didntLike')
    plt.scatter(smallDoses[:,0],smallDoses[:,1],label='smallDoses')
    plt.scatter(largeDoses[:,0],largeDoses[:,1],label='largeDoses')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Number of frequent flyer miles eamed per year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage of time spent playing video games')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=[18,6])
    plt.scatter(didntLike[:,0],didntLike[:,2],label='didntLike')
    plt.scatter(smallDoses[:,0],smallDoses[:,2],label='smallDoses')
    plt.scatter(largeDoses[:,0],largeDoses[:,2],label='largeDoses')
    plt.xlabel('Number of frequent flyer miles eamed per year')
    plt.ylabel('Liters of ice cream consumed per week')
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=[18,6])
    plt.scatter(didntLike[:,1],didntLike[:,2],label='didntLike')
    plt.scatter(smallDoses[:,1],smallDoses[:,2],label='smallDoses')
    plt.scatter(largeDoses[:,1],largeDoses[:,2],label='largeDoses')
    plt.xlabel('Percentage of time spent playing video games')
    plt.ylabel('Liters of ice cream consumed per week')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

def mscatter(x, y, ax=None, m=None, **kw):
    """
    
    parameters:
        x, y - 
        ax - axes
        m - 
        **kw - 
    return:
        sc - `~matplotlib.collections.PathCollection`
    """
    import matplotlib.markers as mmarkers
    if not ax: ax = plt.gca()
    sc = ax.scatter(x, y, **kw)
    if (m is not None) and (len(m) == len(x)):
        paths = []
        for marker in m:
            if isinstance(marker, mmarkers.MarkerStyle):
                marker_obj = marker
            else:
                marker_obj = mmarkers.MarkerStyle(marker)
            path = marker_obj.get_path().transformed(
                marker_obj.get_transform())
            paths.append(path)
        sc.set_paths(paths)
    return sc

def showdatas2(datingDataMat, datingLabels):
    """
    plt.scatter()sizecolor
    parameters:
        datingDataMat - 
        datingLabels - (didntLike - 0, smallDoses - 1, largeDoses - 2)
    """    
    map_marker = {0: 'o', 1: 's', 2: '*'}
    markers = list(map(lambda x: map_marker[x], datingLabels))
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=[18,18])
    
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(311)
    scatter1 = ax1.scatter(datingDataMat[:, 0], datingDataMat[:, 1], s = 30.0 * (np.array(datingLabels) + 1), c = 15.0 * np.array(datingLabels))
    a, b = scatter1.legend_elements()
    b = ['$\\mathdefault {didntLike}$', '$\\mathdefault{smallDoses}$', '$\\mathdefault{largeDoses}$']
    ax1.legend(a, b)
    ax1.set(xlabel='Number of frequent flyer miles eamed per year', ylabel='Percentage of time spent playing video games')
    
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(312)
    mscatter(datingDataMat[:, 0], datingDataMat[:, 2], s = 30.0 * (np.array(datingLabels) + 1), c = 15.0 * np.array(datingLabels), ax = ax2, m = np.array(markers))    
    ax2.legend(a, b)
    ax2.set(xlabel='Number of frequent flyer miles eamed per year', ylabel='Liters of ice cream consumed per week')

    
    ax3 = fig.add_subplot(313)
    ax3.scatter(datingDataMat[:, 1], datingDataMat[:, 2], s = 30.0 * (np.array(datingLabels) + 1), c = 15.0 * np.array(datingLabels), alpha = 0.6)
    ax3.legend(a, b)
    ax3.set(xlabel='Percentage of time spent playing video games', ylabel='Liters of ice cream consumed per week')

    
    plt.show()

def showdatas3(datingDataMat, datingLabels):
    """
    Seaborn
    parameters:
        datingDataMat - 
        datingLabels - (didntLike - 0, smallDoses - 1, largeDoses - 2)
    """
    import seaborn as sns
    data = pd.DataFrame(datingDataMat)
    map_label = {0: 'didntLike', 1: 'smallDoses', 2: 'largeDoses'}
    datingLabels = list(map(lambda x: map_label[x], datingLabels))
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=[18,18])
    
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(311)
    sns.scatterplot(x=0,y=1,data=data,hue=datingLabels, ax=ax1)
    ax1.set(xlabel='Number of frequent flyer miles eamed per year', ylabel='Percentage of time spent playing video games')
    
     
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(312)
    sns.scatterplot(x=0,y=2,data=data,hue=datingLabels, ax=ax2)
    ax2.set(xlabel='Number of frequent flyer miles eamed per year', ylabel='Liters of ice cream consumed per week')

    
    ax3 = fig.add_subplot(313)
    sns.scatterplot(x=1,y=2,data=data,hue=datingLabels, ax=ax3)
    ax3.set(xlabel='Percentage of time spent playing video games', ylabel='Liters of ice cream consumed per week')
    
    plt.show()
